name: thermofun

pre_pr_migrator_status.python39: not solvable: ['Encountered problems while solving.\nProblem: package numpy-1.19.1-py36h5510c5b_0 requires python >=3.6,<3.7.0a0, but none of the providers can be installed\n']

raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.4.1" %}

package:
  name: thermofun
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/thermomod/thermofun/archive/v{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 4f0cf27876a18e9be1c0d882b1ec0a031c41c29d6b6cb541f058ea9be958c2a0

  #git_url: https://dmiron@bitbucket.org/gems4/thermofun.git
  #git_rev: test-17

  #git_url: https://github.com/thermohub/thermofun.git
  #git_rev: master

build:
  number: 1
#  skip: True  # [py2k or osx or c_compiler == 'toolchain_c']
  skip: true  # [win and vc<14]
requirements:
  build:
    - cmake
    - ninja
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}
  host:
    - pybind11
    - nlohmann_json >=3.7.0
    - python
    - chemicalfun >=0.1.7
#    - spdlog =1.10.0
#    - setuptools =59.7.0
    - pybind11-abi
  run:
    - python
#    - spdlog =1.10.0
    - chemicalfun >=0.1.7
    - nlohmann_json >=3.7.0
test:
  imports:
    - thermofun

about:
  home: https://thermohub.org/thermofun/thermofun/
  license: LGPL-3.0-only
  license_family: LGPL
  license_file: COPYING
  summary: Standalone library for calculating temperature and pressure corrections of thermodynamic data for substances and reactions.
  doc_url: https://thermohub.org/thermofun/thermofun/
  dev_url: https://github.com/thermomod/thermofun

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - gdmiron
    - allanleal
